\par A Phase two Water Cycle Study (WCS) has been undertaken by Swindon Borough Council as part of the evidence base for Swindon Borough Council Local Plan 2026. The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5979960 Phase 2 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5469353 WCS}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5979960  confirmed that the growth proposed within the Swindon Borough Local Plan 2026 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13722875 
would not cause a deterioration in Water Framework Directive classification subject to the proposed 
infrastructure upgrades to the foul drainage network and sewage treatment works. This condition will ensure the proposed upgrades are undertaken prior to occupation of the proposed development. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5469353  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5469353\charrsid4401720 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4401720\charrsid4401720 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\insrsid11747953\charrsid11747953 Advice to LPA/Applicant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\ul\insrsid4401720\charrsid11747953 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 The Geology under the site consists of Unprod}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 
uctive Strata and Secondary A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 quifers. There are also a number of small surface watercou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 rses on the site. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 As such we would regard it as moderately sensitive with respect to controlled waters.\line \line We have reviewed the Phase 1 Geo-environmental assess
ment (Brookbanks, Oct 2013, Ref 1335/DS/10) and the Environmental Statement Chapter 13: Ground Conditions (Dave Lock Associates) and would make the following observations.\line \line 
Of greatest concern would be the historic landfill identified in the Phase 1 Geo-en
vironmental assessment and the environmental statement. The Geo-environmental assessment describe areas that have clearly been impacted by hydrocarbon contamination. Given the presence of the historic landfill we cannot agree that there is only a low risk
 to controlled waters. We would certainly require further assessment and investigation of this landfill and the risk that it posed to controlled waters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953  (as requested within the above conditions)}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 . This must include testing of groundwater/leachate beneath the site and of surface watercourses in the vicinity of the landfill.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 \line 
We note that a drainage basin/ditch is shown in the vicinity of the landfill. This is of particular concern as there is the risk that this could mobilise contaminants within the landfill. \line \line 
The presence of a railway and historic canal may also be sources of contamination that could pose some risk to controlled water receptors. There may also be sources of contamination associated with former agricultural usage. \line \line 
With regards to the Environmental Statement, given the presence of a historic landfill we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 would not}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 
 agree with the assessment that there is only a negligible risk to from earth work on site.\line \line In the Geo-environmental assessment and the Environmental Statement we should point out tha
t the old aquifer classification system has been used. At this site there are no major technical differences between the old and the new classification, except that formally the "Non-aquifer" referred to are now classified as "unproductive strata" and "mi
nor Aquifers" and now "Secondary Aquifers".\line \line 
We would wish to make the following comments on Environmental Statement Chapter 12: Water Resources (Dave Lock Associates). We could not agree with the assessment that there is only negligible risk from surface w
ater drainage. While Infiltration SUDs are a important component of pollution control, they may not be suitable in all situation. They may not offer sufficient pollution control in areas where groundwater is particularly shal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 low (less than }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 1m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 etre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484  between b
ase of SUDs and Groundwater) or the potential pollution loading particularly high (such as for a larger road). They may also mobilise contamination present in the ground. This could be of particularly relevance for the area of the former landfill. Further
 detailed assessments of the risks would be required prior to any development on site}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 , as requested in the above conditions}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5596484\charrsid5596484 
. In order to determine sufficient depth to groundwater, some groundwater level moni}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 toring is likely to be required.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13247601\charrsid13247601 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid13247601\charrsid13247601 \line }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11747953 If you have any further questions please don\rquote t hesitate to contact me.
